      "id": "ch-o1-proof",
      "title": "Why is it O(1)?",
      "description": "A friend says 'moving a node to the head requires scanning the list to find it — that's O(n)'. They're wrong. Explain exactly why the combination of HashMap + doubly-linked list makes both get() and put() genuinely O(1). What is each data structure responsible for?",
      "type": "optimize"
    },
